            "en": "<p>In principle, any company can become a service voucher company provided that it obtains recognition. Commercial enterprises as well as non-profit organisations and public social welfare centres can apply for recognition. Your company can either carry out activities exclusively with service vouchers or in addition to other activities.</p><p>In order to become a recognised company, you must meet a number of conditions. For example, you must take part in an information session, pay a deposit of EUR 25,000 and add an accurate business plan in accordance with the regulations on service vouchers. General conditions also apply.</p><p>After obtaining recognition, you have to recruit employees who want to work as service voucher employees. They may also be foreign workers, provided they have a valid work permit. These employees must also meet certain conditions. Certain categories of employees may not be recruited through a service voucher employment contract. In addition, they may only perform a specific number of defined tasks.</p>",
